      "text": "# [[Over-Optimism in Technology]] and the Promotion of the Powerful Man"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "c4bcb843528dc4b0",
      "text": "In discussions around [[climate change]], solutions are often thought of with long time-frames, whether because of the long time scale associated with possible changes in the climate or earth system or because of the long life of infrastructure that provides some [[inertia]] or delays in the implementation of effective measures."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "cd3583f4bce10816",
      "text": "Nevertheless, there is consensus among scientists that we must drastically reduce the\nemission of CO2 and other GHGs in order to achieve carbon neutrality by the middle of our\ncentury and we must stop the destruction of the great forests and oceans, which represent\nimportant sinks in the carbon cycle. In fact, the question today is not so much what we\nshould do but how we should do it. In fact, we live in an epoch in which it is necessary to\nanswer the challenge of how to govern the Earth as a whole [ 21 ], which allows managing\nand protecting the common parts, like a big condominium [22]. Otherwise, as Hardin\nwrote in his well-known article ‘[[Tragedy of Commons]]’, the free use of the commons brings\nruin to all, to the extent that “each man is locked into a system that compels him to increase\nhis herd without limit—in a world that is limited” [23] (p. 1244)."
